Nov 19 2009 	Great location in SF	The location was convenient, and our room on the 5th floor was clean and quiet, though a bit small. The free wifi was great. There's only complimentary coffee and tea, no breakfast. Unfortunately, the water temperature in the shower/tub was hard to control, and a few times the water was too hot. The hotel parking was $21 per day, no multiple entry, so we parked at the AMC 14 up the block, where parking was $19 per day, multiple entry. My favorite of the nearby restaurants was A La Turca for reasonably priced, authentic Turkish food (great eggplant-bell pepper-yogurt appetizer, meat combo dish, Turkish pizza, Turkish tea, and baklava). Walking in the neighborhood at night seemed safe, both alone and together, but as with any big city, it's best to take precautions.	
